name: At the end of the garden

metadata.name: At the end of the garden
metadata.description:
This collection called "At the End of the Garden" is inspired by a part of “Theory and Play Of The Duende” book by “Federico García Lorca”.
It is about longing and living and the death that finally finds us.

in the garden i will die
between the roses-
they will kill me
i was going mother
to pick the roses
to find death
